==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fane
<hw>Fane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>fanum</ets> a
place dedicated to some deity, a sanctuary, fr. <ets>fari</ets> to
speak. See <er>Fame</er>.]</ety> <def>A temple; a place consecrated to
religion; a church.</def> <mark>[Poet.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Such to this British Isle, her Christian <qex>fanes</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fane</ent>⟦br⟧

